<subSubSection pageId="127" pageNumber="886" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="127.[2053,2646,998,1421]" pageId="127" pageNumber="886">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1904" box="[2055,2260,1112,1145]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Scotophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="127" pageNumber="886" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nux">Scotophilus nux</taxonomicName>
has been treated as a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Schreber" baseAuthorityYear="1774" box="[2212,2297,1152,1185]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Scotophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="127" pageNumber="886" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nigrita">nigrita</taxonomicName>
(when 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Schreber" baseAuthorityYear="1774" box="[2419,2504,1152,1185]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Scotophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="127" pageNumber="886" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nigrita">nigrita</taxonomicName>
was used for the species now called S. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="A. Smith" baseAuthorityYear="1833" box="[2460,2568,1191,1224]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Scotophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="127" pageNumber="886" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="dinganii">dinganii</taxonomicName>
) or a subspecies of S. 
<taxonomicName box="[2289,2423,1231,1264]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Scotophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="127" pageNumber="886" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="leucogaster">leucogaster</taxonomicName>
. Based on multivariate analyses of forearm and cranial measurements, it is treated as a distinct species. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
