<subSubSection box="[1444,2530,2022,2055]" pageId="127" pageNumber="886" type="food_feeding">
<paragraph blockId="127.[1442,2650,1433,2607]" box="[1444,2530,2022,2055]" pageId="127" pageNumber="886">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1444,1705,2022,2055]" pageId="127" pageNumber="886">Food and Feeding.</emphasis>
The Nut-colored Yellow Bat apparently forages over water.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="127" pageNumber="886" type="breeding">
<paragraph blockId="127.[1442,2650,1433,2607]" pageId="127" pageNumber="886">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1444,1578,2061,2094]" pageId="127" pageNumber="886">Breeding.</emphasis>
Two Nut-colored Yellow Bats with one fetus each were recorded in March in 
<collectingCountry box="[1481,1632,2101,2134]" name="Democratic Republic of the Congo" pageId="127" pageNumber="886">DR Congo</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="127" pageNumber="886" type="activity">
<paragraph blockId="127.[1442,2650,1433,2607]" pageId="127" pageNumber="886">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1442,1676,2140,2173]" pageId="127" pageNumber="886">Activity patterns.</emphasis>
The Nut-colored Yellow Bat roosts in hollow trees and in small groups in roofs of houses. In western 
<collectingCountry box="[1889,2001,2179,2212]" name="Uganda" pageId="127" pageNumber="886">Uganda</collectingCountry>
, echolocation calls had minimum frequency of 40-7 kHz, maximum frequency of 54-1 kHz, characteristic frequency of 43 kHz, frequency of the knee of 45-1 kHz, and duration of 2 milliseconds. In 
<collectingCountry box="[2456,2552,2266,2291]" name="Gabon" pageId="127" pageNumber="886">Gabon</collectingCountry>
, mean minimum frequency was 38-5 kHz (37-8-40), mean maximum frequency was 59-5 kHz (52-5-75-8), mean dominant frequency was 44-5 kHz (41:1-47-4), mean duration was 1-9 milliseconds (1-6-2-5), and mean interpulse interval was 57-1 milliseconds (16-2-108-6).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
